        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="lb-note">
      <sup>*</sup> OMEGA reports 95.4% task-averaged (mean of per-category scores) as its headline figure;
      93.2% is the raw count (466/500). We cite the raw count for direct comparability with other rows.
    </p>
    <p class="lb-note">
      <strong>AgentMemory excluded:</strong> AgentMemory publishes 96.2% on LongMemEval-S and is a strong
      system worth evaluating. Its run uses <strong>GPT-4o as judge</strong> &mdash; not the LongMemEval
      official gpt-4o-mini judge this leaderboard enforces. Same-judge methodology is the comparability
      discipline here. See their result at
      <a href="https://github.com/JordanMcCann/agentmemory">github.com/JordanMcCann/agentmemory</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lb-section">
    <h2>Beyond accuracy: the engineering matrix</h2>
    <p class="lb-section-intro">
      Same systems, six axes that matter past raw accuracy. Each cell is sourced; cells silent in
